import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Q1 2026 Update — Adam Penn" description="Quarterly founder update: Q1 2026. New fund activity, operational improvements, and reflections on time.">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="page-header">
      <a href="/updates" class="update-back">All Updates</a>
      <h1>Quarterly Founder Update — Q1 2026</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-light);">March 2026</p>
    </div>

    <section class="section update-content">

      <h2>Wins</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Closed a new round for Bidwell Capital Fund with strong investor interest. The fund strategy is resonating — especially the tax-advantaged structures.</li>
        <li>Penn Properties hit its highest occupancy rate to date in Q1. New revenue management systems are paying off.</li>
        <li>Recorded a 10-episode sprint for the podcast with some great guests. The backlog is healthy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Lessons</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>I underestimated how much energy context-switching between ventures takes. I'm experimenting with theme days — dedicating full days to a single business instead of splitting attention.</li>
        <li>Delegation doesn't mean disappearing. The best results come when I set clear systems and then stay close enough to catch drift early.</li>
        <li>Saying no continues to be the highest-leverage skill I'm developing.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I'm Focusing On Next</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Scaling the Bidwell Capital Fund investor community without sacrificing the quality of relationships.</li>
        <li>Hiring a dedicated operations lead for Penn Properties so I can shift more time to fund strategy.</li>
        <li>Rebuilding adampenn.com (you're looking at it).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I'm Reading & Thinking About</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Re-reading <em>The Almanack of Naval Ravikant</em> — the sections on leverage and judgment hit differently now.</li>
        <li>Thinking a lot about the difference between being busy and being productive. They're almost opposites.</li>
        <li>Interested in how other founder-operators structure their time across multiple ventures without burning out.</li>
      </ul>

    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
